rComments: Well, I have to take the class with professor again. Professor always choose to construct her assignments as to make it so difficult for students to merely understand what are the requirements. To ask for clarifications is pointless. She would not explain.
Awesome prof, would take a class with her again
She made summer school fun
Absolutely amazing. A caring, knowledgeable, passionate, engaging prof. Expects work to be well done and on time, but is a fair grader. We're fortunate to have her!
Shes so kind & easy-going.. just follow the syllabus and youll be golden
st paul is lucky to have her, she is one of the best. don't be afraid to ask questions and don't overthink it! she's great, no doubt
Best prof I've ever had.

she's absolutely fabulous, i would definitely recommend her class. you can't expect a free ride, make sure you do your work (ON TIME) and try your best, you will be rewarded. feel free to ask questions after class too
Do NOT expect to get any feedback from her... Would not recommend taking her online course. She never replied to emails and her assignment rubric were not very clear.
AVOID- Professor is unclear in regards to assignments and essays then blames students for missing key points. Textbook is useless.

Prof Dakroury does not respond to her students emails. She changed the syllabus halfway through the course (how is that ok!?). Her quizzes are filled with errors and does not let you see the corrections so you can contest or question. It took over a month to mark our research paper. Her expectations were not aligned with her instructions! AVOID.

DO NOT TAKE! A very difficult professor, in terms of being fair and approachable.  Does not answer e-mails, does not admit mistakes, does not make up for HER mistakes that effect her students.  If you want an unfair grade and more stress, take this class!

Her quizzes are not always clear and can be hard to understand because of the grammar and format issue. This also happens in other writings, emails, articles, etc. She also ignored most of my emails, including the ones about the exam change and marks not showing up. I would avoid taking any classes with her.
Ignores all emails students send her. Clearly lost any passion for teaching. Quizzes unclear. Doesn't care about her students.  DO NOT TAKE

Slow to reply to questions (e-mail or BBLearn), blames lack of clarity on students not paying attention instead of the heavy grammatical issues and formatting. Very slow marking with regards to essays (3 weeks). Refuses to release answer key for past quizzes and insists that it is too difficult/not allowed by faculty. Avoid, esp for  online class.
Quizzes were riddled with grammatical errors which the professor refused to acknowledge until the matter was brought to the Dean. She is unaccommodating and flippant. Avoid her at all costs.

Terrible professor. The assigned textbook, which she co-edited, was full of grammatical errors and typos. The sequence and content of the chapters themselves was completely illogical and there was a lot of repetition. Online multiple choice quizzes extremely poorly written. Essay questions long-winded, poorly worded and baffling. AVOID her.

Prof. Dakroury was an absolutely awful teacher. She is virtually unable to communicate with her students, partly due to her inability to enunciate and mostly because of her unpreparedness. Never cracked the textbook and achieved a B by doing practice quizzes online. Pathetic, appalling show from the University of Ottawa. Terrible lecturer, AVOID!!!

She's so sweet but horrible prof. There are grammar mistakes in the slides, which she doesn't put on VC. She put quizzes online and 80% of the questions from those are the exam questions, but the answers to those questions contradict what it says in the textbook. I'm writing my exam in 4 hours and I don't know if text or quizzes are correct.

She's a sweet lady but I can't believe it's a commie class. She's so out of date (thinks Usher is a main rapper in 2013, and just learnt LOL). It's her textbook (exams are only from the textbook- classes have nothing to do with it) and it's dull to read and makes absolutely no sense. She has a nice heart but I'd rather watch paint dry

Awful. Just awful. So disorganized, doesn't provide her e-mail address so you have to use virtual campus, takes forever to answer. Oh and she lost my midterm and tried to say I didn't write it. Avoid her.

So boring. It's hard to stay focus. Not engaging. She has a good heart and is nice but I couldn't seem to stay interested. She helped write the textbook so exams reflected that. Spelling errors in lecture slides, hard to believe i was sitting in a communications class.

Great prof. Very friendly and interested in the subject matter. Interested in helping students succeed and posted tons of practice quizzes on virtual campus. She often ended classes early and was very relaxed on attendance and lateness. I hope to take another class with her.

Repeated opinion various times and talked about mundane things that made the class seem like a lifetime. Did not explain exam content well even when asked repeatedly by the class. Offered a biased view on the content. Her textbook was co-written by her so each book we were REQUIRED to buy gave her money. Horrible representation of this university.

Doesn't put the slides on virtual campus so you have to go to class. Hard to understand at times. Answers e-mails fairly quickly... but is unclear at times. She's helpful with the use of online quizes to prepare for exams. Really nice lady who tries really hard to make the class interesting... by refering to lady gaga almost every class.

She is well intentioned and makes her expectations for assignments clear. But I didn't find her lectures stimulating or engaging. In particular, her delivery of the material was unenthusiastic and her foreign accent made concepts hard to understand. Overall she is an average professor.

Nice women, but not what I would hope for in a 3rd year class.  Learned a fair amount only because of the journals and reading articles.  Easy A, but you might not learn much from her, unless its about Al Jazeera and Muslims

Being in my last year of studies, Prof. Dakroury by all means one of the most amazing professors I met at the university. very clear expectations, real-life examples, and very interesting videos!! highly recommended :)
I love her passion about media studies and found her lectures very useful. I liked the online quizzes that prepared me for the mid-term. an A+ professor

This class could have been intersting. She spends most of the class lecturing on how students should be and not on the actual class material. She post questions online and makes her test from these questions. So, it is an easy class. If you want an A dont go to class and just do the questions online.
a wonderful professor, very approachable, knowledgeable, and super nice! what I like best is how she is always available and very fast in responding to my questions and emails :)

This prof is pretty awful. The class is an easy A, but if you want to learn anything it's useless. Her English speaking and writing abilities impede comprehension, she's very biased, and she assigns reading journals every week (and the focus question only sometimes makes sense, and even more rarely is actually related to the readings). Avoid!
Very cute, nice and sweet.
Don't buy the textbook!!!!! It's her own book and is useless and very bias. Her slides have no information either, so if you miss class, you are not missing anything...

I had her for two classes: Media Ethics 3105 and Theories of Comm 3109. Same textbook, same content. You don't really need to go to classes, she's very nice and accommodating. It's impossible to fail -- it's easy material and her assignments are straight forward and right from the text book. Take her if you can!

Prof is really nice and doesn't have midterms, but her slides are too fast and she doesn't post, and makes you buy her book (Don't buy it, it doesn't help. It makes things worse) Also she uses the same TA for all her classes and her TA is a really really tough marker. Very particular about APA styling and easy to lose a lot of marks for that.OkProf
